    DEPENDENCIES
        - Python version >= 2.2
        - JNI >= 1.2 (untested, preferably 1.4)

    BUILDING ON LINUX/UNIX
        Make sure you have JAVA_HOME set, then simply ./configure && make.

    BUILDING ON MAC OS X

    You'll need:
        - To set JAVA_HOME to /Library/Java/Home
        - To compile Python or download it using Fink.
        - The developer kits from Apple with gcc and Java development
        - You'll need to make a symlink from libjep.dynlib to /Library/Java/Extentions, like:
            sudo ln -s `pwd`/.libs/libjep.dylib /Library/Java/Extensions/libjep.jnilib

    AUTOMAKE 1.6
        If you're using automake > 1.4, please run the `autogen.sh` script before running configure. This includes Mac OS X.

